items.name: E-Sport Stage Concept
items.description:
The term "E-Sport Stage Concept" generally refers to the design and setup of a physical stage or arena for esports (electronic sports) events.

Esports has gained significant popularity over the years, and professional tournaments and competitions often take place in large venues with elaborate stage setups to provide an engaging and immersive experience for both the live audience and online viewers.

items.name: Chibi Style - Komowata Haruka (Yuzusoft)
items.description:
Style LoHa based on the works of Komowata Haruka, the prolific visual novel SD illustrator and artist, whose work is often seen in Yuzusoft titles.

Usage

Weight 0.5~0.9 works okay. Vary it depending on how strong you want the style and/or how much detail you want to keep.

For use with CounterfeitXL-Î². I can't guarantee it will work well on other checkpoints.

Add chibi to positive for chibi style proportions, add to negative if you want the art style but not the chibi proportions.

Non-commercial use only. Also, play Riddle Joker.

items.description:
Files Detail

AYWildcards.zip

  • LipsColor.zip -> Contain Wildcards (.txt)

    • pink_colors_count = 16

    • red_colors_count = 10

    • mauve_colors_count = 5

    • plum_colors_count = 10

    • terra_cotta_colors_count = 7

    • brown_colors_count = 5

    • orange_colors_count = 7

    • berry_colors_count = 7

    • natural_colors_count = 14

  • Weight.zip -> Contain Wildcards (.txt)

    • N1 = -1.0 to 0.0

    • N2 = -2.0 to 0.0

    • N3 = -3.0 to 0.0

    • N4 = -4.0 to 0.0

    • N5 = -5.0 to 0.0

    • P1 = 0.0 to 1.0

    • P2 = 0.0 to 2.0

    • P3 = 0.0 to 3.0

    • P4 = 0.0 to 4.0

    • P5 = 0.0 to 5.0

    • N1P1 = -1.0 to 1.0

    • N2P2 = -2.0 to 2.0

    • N3P3 = -3.0 to 3.0

    • N4P4 = -4.0 to 4.0

    • N5P5 = -5.0 to 5.0

  • SomePlaceLocation.zip -> Contain Wildcards (.txt)

    • Beach = 10

    • Cities = 20

    • CulturalNHistorical = 10

    • HistoricDistricts = 10

    • Landmarks = 10

    • NationalParks = 10

    • NaturalWonders = 10

      • Total = 80

    • Rivers = 10

    • WaterFallTypes = 10

    • ForestTypes = 10

      • Total = 30


How to use?

  • I assume you have "Wildcards Extension"
    (my personal recommend : https://github.com/adieyal/sd-dynamic-prompts) thanks author

    • If not you need to look for Extension Tab of WebUI or else

    • Extension -> Available -> Load from: Button -> Search for Dynamic prompts or Wildcards

  • Extract folders/files into wildcards folder (default for dynamic-prompts? : SD Folder\extensions\sd-dynamic-prompts\wildcards)

  • Write prompt and lets go wild!!

Example Usage

P is Positive

items.name: Tom Wesselmann SDXL 1.0 art style LoRA
items.description:
If you like what I do please consider supporting me on Patreon and contributing your ideas to my future projects!

Tom Wessselmann art style lora for SDXL 1.0. Tom Wessselmann is a American pop art artist and now you can generate art similar to his style within your own Stable Diffusion workflow. This model was trained on 1024 x 1024 and is able to produce higher details and greater accuracy than if you were to simply type his name into your prompt. You can however add "in the style of Tom Wesselmann" to your prompt in addition to the <lora> and trigger for a slightly different effect.

I use this at a weight of around 1 but you may have to adjust the weight up or down to 0.8 incrementally depending on the complexity of your prompt. I used clip skip 1 for all of the images you see uploaded to this page. CFG 11 works good for this art style.

The main trigger is w3ss and some additional tags are:
woman,
white border,
still life,
face

Have fun playing around with this remarkable tech and if you like it be sure to review and upload all of your amazing works of art!

How to Use This Model

USE THEM SIMULTANEOUSLY. In this case, you need to download both focalors_genshin.pt and focalors_genshin.safetensors, then use focalors_genshin.pt as texture inversion embedding, and use focalors_genshin.safetensors as LoRA at the same time.

The trigger word is focalors_genshin, and the recommended tags are masterpiece, best quality, highres, solo, {focalors_genshin:1.10}, blue_eyes, hat, blue_hair, white_hair, bangs, hair_between_eyes, bow, smile, ahoge, long_hair, multicolored_hair, blue_headwear.

How This Model Is Trained

This model is trained with HCP-Diffusion. And the auto-training framework is maintained by DeepGHS Team.

Why Some Preview Images Not Look Like Focalors Genshin

All the prompt texts used on the preview images (which can be viewed by clicking on the images) are automatically generated using clustering algorithms based on feature information extracted from the training dataset. The seed used during image generation is also randomly generated, and the images have not undergone any selection or modification. As a result, there is a possibility of the mentioned issues occurring.

In practice, based on our internal testing, most models that experience such issues perform better in actual usage than what is seen in the preview images. The only thing you may need to do is fine-tune the tags you use.

I Felt This Model May Be Overfitting or Underfitting, What Shall I Do

Our model has been published on huggingface repository - CyberHarem/focalors_genshin, where models of all the steps are saved. Also, we published the training dataset on huggingface dataset - CyberHarem/focalors_genshin, which may be helpful to you.

Why Not Just Using The Better-Selected Images

Our model's entire process, from data crawling, training, to generating preview images and publishing, is 100% automated without any human intervention. It's an interesting experiment conducted by our team, and for this purpose, we have developed a complete set of software infrastructure, including data filtering, automatic training, and automated publishing. Therefore, if possible, we would appreciate more feedback or suggestions as they are highly valuable to us.

items.name: ClassipeintXL (oil paint style LoRA)
items.description:
ClassipeintXL - truly the final version (I'm 99% confident)

please consider sharing some of your images with this LoRA - I'd love to see them!

also now checkout the companion LoRAs LaxpeintXL for a more digital painting look and ParchartXL for that perfect parchment texture you've been looking for.

This lightweight LoRA brings a consistent appearance of richly textured oil painting. With a blend of various Western painting traditions, it feels familiar and timeless.

Version 1.8 is a merge of the first, third, and a previously unshared version of this LoRA - strengths from each iteration are all in full effect here, and biases are minimized. This is by far the most consistent, easiest LoRA for generating images with SDXL that capture the feel of genuine oil paintings for whatever subject matter you want to prompt.

Recommended settings for use:

You can go here (pastebin) to download a ComfyUI workflow like what I used, but without custom nodes that are embedded in my image uploads on CivitAI.

  • Start with a full 1.0 LoRA strength and adjust down to 0.7 or 0.8 for a subtler painterly effect. You can adjust upward (to 1.2 or maybe a little more) to maximize the painterly appearance, but it can start to introduce some quirks

  • Use the LoRA with your preferred SDXL model with no refiner. I have so far just stuck with base SDXL1.0 but other finetunes work great as well.

  • I recommend the DPM samplers, but use your favorite. Some may produce softer painting styles that don't suit my taste as much but whatever you prefer is great.

  • Don't do anything special for your prompt - just describe what you want to see. I usually prompt 'by ClassipeintXL' but you don't really need to use any keywords unless some subject matter seems to override the LoRA's style, then you can bring it back in line by using the terms "oil painting of..." and "by ClassipeintXL".

  • Feel free to add artist names (Klimt, Mucha, etc) and the LoRA will merge its style with theirs with usually fantastic results.

I'm happy to share my work for free, just as the base model SDXL came free to us all. But if you felt compelled to offer some material form of thanks, you can buy me a coffee, or you can buy my (darn near unreadable, I warn you) short story 'Willem & Ellene'.

items.name: Lana del Rey Embedding
items.description: Elizabeth Woolridge Grant (born June 21, 1985), known professionally as Lana Del Rey, is an American singer-songwriter. Her music is noted for its cinematic quality and exploration of tragic romance, glamour, and melancholia, with frequent references to contemporary pop culture and 1950sâ€“1970s Americana. She is the recipient of various accolades, including two Brit Awards, two Billboard Women in Music, two MTV Europe Music Awards, and a Satellite Award, in addition to nominations for six Grammy Awards and a Golden Globe Award. Variety honored her at their Hitmakers Awards for being "one of the most influential singer-songwriters of the 21st century". Rolling Stone placed Del Rey in their list of 200 Greatest Singers of All Time (2023), and also Rolling Stone UK named her The Greatest American Songwriter of the 21st century (2023). Time magazine named Del Rey one of the 100 most influential people in the world in 2012.

items.name: Rosedoodle 2-in-1 [Character, Style]
items.description:
Lora for the cat sprout vtuber, Rosedoodle. Check her out on Twitch or one of her gazillion socials

Does her default outfit with and without jacket, maid outfit, and can also do her 3d model's style. Only does her older design & style, and not her redesign.

Activates with "rosedoodle (vtuber)", works at strength 1. Trained at 640x640 on NAI leak.

In addition to your normal positives and negatives, the following tags work well, with positives first, and then negatives:

  • Rosedoodle (base/custom outfit):

    • rosedoodle (vtuber), hair ornament, hair flower, virtual youtuber, indie virtual youtuber, green hair, cat girl, tail, side ponytail, ahoge

    • twintails, jpeg_artifacts, yellow_eyes, blue_eyes, flat color, 3d, cel shading

      • Use these tags along with whatever outfit you want

  • Crop top w/hoodie

    • defaultoutfit, (crop top:1.1), jacket, open jacket, multicolored clothes, bike shorts, thong, thighhighs, mismatched_legwear, asymmetrical_legwear

    • pants, socks

  • Crop top, no hoodie

    • defaultoutfit, (crop top:1.1), bare shoulders, multicolored clothes, bike shorts, thong, thighhighs, mismatched legwear, asymmetrical legwear

    • pants, jacket, hood, hoodie, socks, off_shoulder

      • Do not put 'single detached sleeve' in the prompt, it will make two sleeves almost every time

  • Maid outfit

    • maidoutfit, maid headdress, pantyhose, back bow, cleavage, wrist cuffs, puffy short sleeves

    • panties

  • 3d model's style

    • 3d, flat color, cel shading

    • no negative prompt

      • Unless you specifically want her 3d style, these tags should always be in negatives, otherwise they will affect the style anyway. Just don't forget to take them out of negatives if you do want them

      • Makes lighting & backgrounds worse

misc notes:

Her different accessories and hairstyles (twintails, long hair, tail bow, scrunchie, necklace, etc) are also tagged, so feel absolutely free to try more tags & combinations than what I've listed

Beepu doesn't really show up unprompted, but if you want to put him in negatives (or positives, for some reason??), you can use 'beepu, stuffed toy, mascot'

Her funky eyes don't work properly, but if you want to give them a shot anyway, they're tagged as 'symbol-shaped pupils, flower-shaped pupils'. Using the 3d style gets it a little better

Inpaint will get her accessories and outfits right very easily, especially if you use inpaint sketch or image editors, which is handy because the lora is a little gacha

Why do this?

  1. Basic theory: Realistic model is better for human body structure, animation model is better for movement and more artistic, I hope to get the advantages of both.

  2. Use the realistic base model as the overall base model, use LORA to adjust the format of the drawing from 3D-PHOTO--->2D-DRAW.

  3. Adjust LORA parameters to find the sweet point.

V2.0
After understanding the LECO training method, we will adjust the parameters and the learning rate in order to achieve better results with smaller files and fewer weights.

The available weights are from +2 to -2, and the recommended weights are from +2 to -1.0, with positive values providing animation tendency and negative values providing real tendency.

The performance of positive weight (animation) is better than negative weight (real).

The Ghost Festival is a traditional Chinese festival celebrated on the 15th day of the seventh month in the lunar calendar. It is a time to remember and honor the dead, and to pray for their well-being.

The festival is said to have originated in China during the Qin dynasty (221â€“206 BC). At that time, the Qin emperor ordered the burning of all books and the burying of all scholars. This led to a widespread belief that the dead were angry and vengeful. The Ghost Festival was created as a way to appease the dead and to prevent them from causing harm to the living.

The Ghost Festival is celebrated in many different ways throughout Asia. In China, people often set up altars in their homes and businesses to offer food, drinks, and incense to the dead. They may also visit the tombs of their ancestors and clean them. In Taiwan, people often participate in parades and performances that feature ghosts and other supernatural beings. In Japan, people often visit temples and shrines to pray for the dead.

The Ghost Festival is a time to reflect on the past and to remember those who have passed away. It is also a time to hope for a better future for the living and the dead.

The Ghost Festival is a time for both joy and sorrow. It is a time to remember those who have passed away, and to hope for a better future for the living and the dead.

items.name: All4All
items.description:
A lot of details, a variety of compositions, the emphasis is on small details, buildings, cyberpunk stylistics, close-ups, anime animals, watercolor drawings and much more

I made a video on how to achieve the same quality or just repeat my art

P.S. If you want to support me, then you can subscribe to my Patreon and get builds earlier than they come out here (versions on patreon will always be newer by one than here) This will help me a lot in updating the video card over time to make models even better and faster (the main thing is better)

Eta noise seed delta 31337

LORA weight 0.5-0.6

Use Abyssorangemix3aom3_aom3a3.safetensors With these negative prompts:
(worst quality, low quality, extra digits:1.4) or (worst quality, low quality:1.4)



just use hires fix as much as your video card is capable of, so as not to give an error, with 8gb of video memory it is 512x768 with hires fix 2-2.15, upscaler Latent (nearest-exact), the picture will be much more detailed. If you want a style close to the original but with more detail, don't use Denoising strength above 0.6, but to avoid artifacts, do not use too low a value, optimally 0.5

CFG Scale - 5-7

The training took place at a resolution of 512x768, so it makes no sense to use 512x512

Combined with my other LORA

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

    *Information taken from Lykon

    Please post your work with or without comments, it will help me improve. Thanks!

    If you like my work, click on the heart above, I will be pleased :3

items.name: CartoonCraft
items.description:
This is a simple utility LoRA for ComicCraft. Since ComicCraft focuses on comic and fantasy styles, they often have too many details to produce something that is closer to a cartoon or animation style and controlling it with just prompt can take some time.

What this LoRA does is to simplify images, mainly by flattening colors (less gradients), reduce ink shadow effects and reduce the amount and strength of lines (both outlines and internal details), so it can be closer to that animation style.

It works well for this purpose with weights between 0.75 and 1, but higher values will keep simplifying the images. Negative values will technically add more details, but will become noisy.

It has been tested with other models and it works well too. For example used on realistic models, results become more semi-realistic illustrations and you can use higher weights to obtain results that are more like cartoons.

The tags from the base ComicCraft should still be available, but will also be simplified.

Regarding the showcase images, I didn't use Hires fix and tried to use examples from other similar models so it can be used for comparison.
